{type:"numerical",text:"Two identical conducting spheres carry charges of 17 microC and -18 microC. After they touch and separate, find the charge (in microC) on each sphere.",answer:-0.5,solution:"Total charge = 17+(-18) = -1 microC, shared equally: -0.5 microC each."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A dipole of moment 11 (in SI-scaled units) is placed in a uniform electric field of magnitude 70 (in matching units) at an angle of 30 degrees to the field. Find the torque (in the corresponding units) on it.",answer:385.0,solution:"Torque = pE sin(theta) = 11x70x0.5 = 385.0."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A dipole of moment 11 (in SI-scaled units) is placed in a uniform electric field of magnitude 140 (in matching units) at an angle of 60 degrees to the field. Find the torque (in the corresponding units) on it.",answer:1333.64,solution:"Torque = pE sin(theta) = 11x140x0.866 = 1333.64."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A capacitor of capacitance 5 microF is charged to a potential of 186 V. Find the energy stored (in J).",answer:0.0865,solution:"U = (1/2)CV^2 = 0.5x5x10^-6x186^2 = 0.0865 J."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A capacitor of capacitance 10 microF is charged to a potential of 142 V. Find the energy stored (in J).",answer:0.1008,solution:"U = (1/2)CV^2 = 0.5x10x10^-6x142^2 = 0.1008 J."},
{type:"numerical",text:"Two identical conducting spheres carry charges of 4 microC and -18 microC. After they touch and separate, find the charge (in microC) on each sphere.",answer:-7.0,solution:"Total charge = 4+(-18) = -14 microC, shared equally: -7.0 microC each."},
{type:"numerical",text:"Find the electric potential (in units of 10^3 V) at a distance of 2 m from a point charge of 2 microC (k=9x10^9 N m^2/C^2).",answer:9.0,solution:"V = kq/r = 9x10^9x2x10^-6/2 = 9000.0 V = 9.0 x 10^3 V."},
{type:"numerical",text:"4 identical capacitors of 3 microF each are connected in series. Find the equivalent capacitance (in microF).",answer:0.75,solution:"For n identical capacitors in series, Ceq = C/n = 3/4 = 0.75 microF."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A dipole of moment 18 (in SI-scaled units) is placed in a uniform electric field of magnitude 65 (in matching units) at an angle of 37 degrees to the field. Find the torque (in the corresponding units) on it.",answer:702.0,solution:"Torque = pE sin(theta) = 18x65x0.6 = 702.0."},
{type:"numerical",text:"3 identical capacitors of 2 microF each are connected in series. Find the equivalent capacitance (in microF).",answer:0.67,solution:"For n identical capacitors in series, Ceq = C/n = 2/3 = 0.67 microF."},
{type:"numerical",text:"2 identical capacitors of 8 microF each are connected in series. Find the equivalent capacitance (in microF).",answer:4.0,solution:"For n identical capacitors in series, Ceq = C/n = 8/2 = 4.0 microF."},
{type:"numerical",text:"Two point charges of 5 microC and 2 microC are placed 0.2 m apart in vacuum. Find the force between them (in N) (k=9x10^9 N m^2/C^2).",answer:2.25,solution:"F = kq1q2/r^2 = 9x10^9 x 5x10^-6 x 2x10^-6 / 0.2^2 = 2.25 N."},
{type:"numerical",text:"A point charge of 4 microC is at the origin. Find the electric field (in units of 10^3 N/C) at a point 4 m away (k=9x10^9 N m^2/C^2).",answer:2.25,solution:"E = kq/r^2 = 9x10^9x4x10^-6/4^2 = 2250.0 N/C = 2.25 x 10^3 N/C."}
